  "base_commit": "7ce57873cfc177fa683ccb6bb8fc90eb6dcbef7e",
  "pr_number": 3222,
  "issue_number": 3221,
  "issue_title": "Implement the Archenemy Schemes subsystem (CR 904 / CR 701.32 Set in Motion)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n**Scheme** cards are unsupported. `CoreType` (`crates/engine/src/types/card_type.rs`) has **no `Scheme` variant**, and there is no scheme deck, no \"set the top scheme in motion\" turn step, and no ongoing-scheme / `abandon` runtime. Notably, the **set-in-motion trigger is already recognized** by the parser but has no resolver \u2014 the exact \"stub, no runtime\" shape that made Meld a clean coverage gap.\n\n## Evidence the stub exists (verified)\n`crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_trigger.rs` already maps the scheme trigger text to a typed mode:\n```rust\nif matches!(lower,\n    \"when you set this scheme in motion\" | \"whenever you set this scheme in motion\"\n) {\n    def.mode = TriggerMode::SetInMotion;\n    return Some((TriggerMode::SetInMotion, def));\n}\n```\nSo `TriggerMode::SetInMotion` is recognized, but nothing **sets a scheme in motion** at runtime, and Scheme cards have no core type \u2014 so the trigger never fires and the cards are unsupported.\n\n## What it is (CR, verified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`)\n- **CR 904 (Archenemy)** \u2014 the archenemy has a **scheme deck**. At the start of the archenemy's turn (before the untap step), they **set the top scheme in motion** (turn it face up in the command zone).\n- **Ongoing schemes** stay face up and apply their abilities until their condition abandons them; non-ongoing schemes are abandoned after they resolve.\n- **CR 701.33 (Abandon)** \u2014 put an abandoned scheme on the bottom of its owner's scheme deck.\n\n## Current behavior\nScheme cards parse with no core type; the recognized `TriggerMode::SetInMotion` never fires because no scheme is ever set in motion. The cards do nothing.\n\n## Correct behavior\nA scheme deck exists per archenemy. At the start of the archenemy's turn, the top scheme is set in motion (face up in the command zone), firing its `SetInMotion` trigger. Ongoing schemes apply their continuous/triggered abilities until abandoned; others abandon on resolution (CR 701.33).\n\n## Affected cards\n~**52** Scheme cards (approximate \u2014 from regenerated card-data; committed data is stale, see the data-staleness issue). Examples: Nature Demands an Offering, Fear My Authority, Your Nightmares Are Delicious.\n**Format note:** Archenemy is a casual variant \u2014 **0 constructed-legal.** Value is format completeness.\n\n## Design (reuse the dungeon/command-zone subsystem pattern)\n- **`CoreType::Scheme`** (+ `Supertype::Ongoing`) in `types/card_type.rs` with parse/display/serde.\n- **A new `game/archenemy.rs` (or `game/schemes.rs`) subsystem** mirroring `game/dungeon.rs`: the scheme deck zone, the command-zone active-scheme slot, the begin-turn \"set in motion\" step, and the `abandon` action.\n- **Wire the existing `TriggerMode::SetInMotion`** so it fires when a scheme is set in motion (the parser side is already done).\n- Reuse the layer/trigger systems for ongoing-scheme statics and abandon conditions.\n\n### Proposed file plan\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `crates/engine/src/types/card_type.rs` | add `CoreType::Scheme` (+ `Ongoing` supertype) + parse/display/serde |\n| `crates/engine/src/game/archenemy.rs` (NEW) | scheme deck zone, set-in-motion turn step, ongoing-scheme tracking, `abandon` (CR 701.33) |\n| `game/turns.rs` | begin-of-turn \"set the top scheme in motion\" step for the archenemy |\n| `game/triggers.rs` / `game/trigger_index.rs` | fire the existing `TriggerMode::SetInMotion` on set-in-motion |\n| `crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_*.rs` | recognize ongoing-scheme statics + \"when this scheme is abandoned\" if needed (nom combinators) |\n| tests (separate `*_tests.rs`) | set-in-motion fires the trigger; ongoing scheme applies until abandoned; non-ongoing abandons on resolution |\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `CoreType::Scheme` parses and round-trips through serde.\n- [ ] A scheme deck exists; the archenemy sets the top scheme in motion at the start of their turn, firing `TriggerMode::SetInMotion`.\n- [ ] Ongoing schemes stay face up and apply their abilities until abandoned; non-ongoing schemes abandon on resolution (CR 701.33).\n- [ ] Building-block tests (not single-card replay) for set-in-motion, ongoing application, and abandon.\n\n## Deferrals (strict-failure / follow-up)\n- Frontend command-zone/active-scheme display.\n- Multi-archenemy / shared-deck nuances if the multiplayer model needs extension.\n- Per-scheme long-tail effect bodies (parser follow-ups).\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-14T17:28:24.000Z",
